title: NASA’s Stakeholder Collaborations Help Inform Moon to Mars Planning
summary: NASA Releases Revised Moon to Mars Objectives

title: NASA set for “kinder, gentler” SLS tanking test
summary: NASA officials say they’re ready to try a new approach to fueling the Space Launch System to prevent the return of leaks that scrubbed an earlier launch attempt even though they are not certain what caused that leak.

title: New report raises questions on DoD’s multi-orbit plan for space sensors
summary: Aerospace Corp. report: 'The missile warning and tracking programs will weigh heavily in debates about the future of U.S. space systems'

title: SAIC to build small satellites with startup Rogue Space
summary: SAIC is partnering with startup Rogue Space Systems to develop small satellites for in-space services, the companies announced Sept. 20.

title: Space Force shifting resources to intelligence and cybersecurity
summary: The U.S. Space Operations Command is assigning cybersecurity and intelligence specialists to work side-by-side with satellite operators so they’re better prepared to protect U.S. systems from electronic and physical threats, said Maj. Gen. Douglas Schiess.
